{
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Criticality Audit & Auto-Test Suite",
  "description": "Triggered after a task involving new code. Kiro analyzes the newly created components to determine if they handle business-critical logic (Auth, Payments, Data Transformation, or Complex UI State). If deemed critical, Kiro is required to generate a comprehensive testing suite (Unit/Integration) before the task is considered complete.",
  "when": {
    "type": "postTaskExecution"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Evaluate all new components created in this task for Criticality.\n\nDiscern: Is this component 'Critical'? (Criteria: Handles sensitive data, complex state logic, external API interactions, or core business rules).\n\nDecision: If NOT critical no need to do anything\n\nAction: If CRITICAL, you must immediately generate a testing suite (using the project's standard framework, e.g., Jest, Vitest, or Cypress).\n\nCoverage: Ensure the tests cover:\n\nHappy path execution.\n\nEdge case handling (null values, timeouts).\n\nError state rendering.\n\nFinal Check: Confirm the tests pass locally before updating the DevOps ticket."
  }
}